Name: ACTION.RESETS.GENERAL
Description: general reset (ddr3 memory controller not included)

Name: STATUS.SFP.ANY_DOWN
Description: reads '1' when any of the enabled SFP ports is down

Name: STATUS.LOCAL_TRIG.CONTINUOUS_ON
Description: continous local L1A on (setup with register 0x1c)

Name: ACTION.LOCAL_TRIG.SEND_ECR
Description: sends event number reset thru TTC when in local L1A mode

Name: ACTION.LOCAL_TRIG.SEND_OCR
Description: sends orbit number reset thru TTC when in local L1A mode

Name: ACTION.LOCAL_TRIG.CONTINUOUS
Description: set continuous local L1A (setup with register 0x1c)

Name: CONF.DIAG.DISABLE_EVB
Description: if '1', pauses event building. For debugging only

Name: CONF.DIAG.MEMTEST_COUNTER
Description: if '0', memory test uses 64bit PRBS. If '1', uses 32 bit sequencial numbers.

Name: CONF.LOCAL_TRIG.FAKE_DATA_ENABLE
Description: if '1', generate fake event upon receiving L1A

Name: CONF.DIAG.FAKE_TTC_ENABLE
Description: if '1', TTS output is 80MHz clock which can be looped back to TTC input

Name: CONF.DIAG.TTS_TEST_ENABLE
Description: if '1', TTS test mode (outputs from TTS_TEST_PATTERN)

Name: CONF.EVB.FLUSH_ON_RESYNC
Description: if '1', send all data to downstream when ttc reset is received\n if '0', flush all data when ttc reset is received.

Name: CONF.EVB.MON_FULL_STOP_EVB
Description: if '1', monitor buffer full will stop event builder

Name: CONF.EVB.SET_MON_PRESCALE
Description: scale factor( = contents + 1). Note: if bit 18 is set to '1', these bits are ignored.

Name: CONF.EVB.SELECT_MASKED_EVN
Description: Value n=0..15, save events with EvN low (20-n) bits '0'

Name: CONF.EVB.ENABLE_MASKED_EVN
Description: If set to '1', bit 22-19 determine which events will be saved

Name: STATUS.SFP0.SFP_LSC_DOWN_MASK
Description: '1' when DAQLSC of SFP0..2 is down

Name: STATUS.SFP_LSC_DOWN_MASK
Description: '1' when DAQLSC of SFP0..2 is down

Name: STATUS.SFP1.SFP_LSC_DOWN_MASK
Description: '1' when DAQLSC of SFP0..2 is down

Name: STATUS.SFP2.SFP_LSC_DOWN_MASK
Description: '1' when DAQLSC of SFP0..2 is down

Name: CONF.AMC.BC0_COMPENSATION
Description: AMC set BC0 compensation, default to 0x18

Name: CONF.ID.SOURCE_ID
Description: CMS Source ID for output data

Name: CONF.BC0_WORKS_ONLY_ONCE
Description: if '1'', TTC BC0 command works only once after reset

Name: CONF.CAL_WINDOW_LOWER_PROG
Description: settable part of calibration window lower limit,3456 minimum(not included), default to '011101'

Name: CONF.CAL_WINDOW_LOWER
Description: read only entire lower window limit

Name: CONF.CAL_WINDOW_UPPER_PROG
Description: settable part of calibration window upper limit,3519 maximum(included), default to '100110'

Name: CONF.CAL_WINDOW_UPPER
Description: read only entire upper window limit

Name: CONF.CAL_ENABLE
Description: Enable calibration events in orbit gap (HCAL), default '1'

Name: STATUS.DIAG.DDR_STATUS_LO
